The paper deals with voting systems and strategic behavior of voters, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The use of iterative voting and the analysis of cycles suggests a potential application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in optimizing voting systems. The paper also involves the manipulation of data and the use of algorithms to analyze the results, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of voter behavior on the outcome of the election, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
